# Rasm C# Testing

Read `.claude/skills/cs-testing/SKILL.md`, `tests/csharp/AGENTS.md`, and nearest test `AGENTS.md`.

## Rail split

| Rail | Owns |
| --- | --- |
| xUnit + `Rasm.TestKit` | Pure-managed behavior, law-matrix specs |
| `*.verify.csx` + bridge | Native Rhino/GH2 runtime paths |
| Architecture tests | Assembly dependency direction only |
| Benchmarks and fuzz | Separate executables, not xUnit |

## Oracles

- Prefer closed-form math, fixture geometry, metamorphic laws, or independent `Numeric` oracles.
- Never mirror current implementation output as expected value.
- Use `Spec.ForAll`, `Spec.Cases`, `Spec.Metamorphic`, `Gens`, and `Numeric`; promote to `_testkit` only after multiple consumers.
- Use `Gen.Where(...).Select(...)` or lifted `Fin` filtering, never `Select+throw`.

## Bridge scenarios

- Path: `tests/csharp/libs/<Project>/<MirrorPath>/scenarios/*.verify.csx`
- Source-only: no `#r`, `#load`, or absolute paths
- Group related checks per file (3–8s Rhino handshake each run)
- Author with `Scenario.Run("theme", CAPTURE_PATH, (key, facts) => { ... });`
- Populate evidence with `facts.Add(string key, object value);`
- Do not call `BridgeMarker.EmitFact`, `BridgeMarker.EmitScenarioHeader`, or per-fact `Console.WriteLine("key=value")`.

## Validation ladder

Run `bash scripts/test.sh` for managed specs. Use `TEST_TARGET=<csproj> bash scripts/test.sh` for non-default projects. Run `bash scripts/rhino.sh verify <scenario-or-glob>` only for bridge-owned runtime behavior.
